'''Jean {{Conjecture|Elaine Grey}}''' was a former ally of [[Wolverine]] and a member of the [[X-Men/Mutant Genocide|X-Men]].

==Biography==
===Member of the X-Men===
====Recruited====
{{Quote|Wanted me to be part of the [[X-Men/Mutant Genocide|team]]. Told them they all looked fucking ridiculous. I couldn’t have them thinking I wanted to be there.|[[Wolverine]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Jean was a [[mutant]] who was recruited by [[Professor X/Mutant Genocide|Charles Xavier]] into the [[X-Men/Mutant Genocide|X-Men]], consisting of her, [[Cyclops/Mutant Genocide|Cyclops]], [[Beast/Mutant Genocide|Beast]] and [[Storm/Mutant Genocide|Storm]]. They were also joined by another mutant named [[Logan]], whom they provided with a [[Wolverine Suit|suit]], although he refused to wear it.{{Ref|DW}}

====[[Massacre at the X-Mansion]]====
{{Quote|And then one day, while I was off on my own, the [[humans]] came. They went [[mutant]] hunting.|[[Wolverine]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Jean and the [[X-Men/Mutant Genocide|X-Men]] were at the [[X-Mansion]] one day when a group of [[Humans|humans]] with anti-[[mutants|mutant]] sentiment arrived and massacred all the mutants inside, including Jean.{{Ref|DW}}

===Legacy===
{{Quote|Mr. Wilson, this [[Wolverine]] let down his [[Mutant Genocide Universe|entire world]]. He's the stuff of legend, but not in a good way. And what he did... Well, some things are just beyond forgiveness.|[[Mr. Paradox]] to [[Deadpool]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
[[Logan]], who had not been inside the [[X-Mansion]] as he was at a bar, returned to find Jean and the other [[X-Men/Mutant Genocide|X-Men]] murdered. The death of Jean put Logan on the path of vengeance, which resulted in the deaths of many [[humans]], both innocent and culpable. Logan eventually ended his tirade but was branded as a monstrous figure, leading him to be shunned by society. Through the actions of [[Deadpool]], Logan found closure and migrated to [[Earth-10005|Deadpool's universe]].{{Ref|DW}}

==Powers==
<!--Do not specify mutant powers. They were never stated within the MCU.-->
*'''Mutant Physiology''': As a [[mutant]], Jean Grey possessed unique DNA structure, different from [[humans]], which granted her superhuman abilities.

